<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,276,675,701]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,374,718,744]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Wingspan: 
<quantity box="[284,369,718,744]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Transverse lines: antemedial line well marked, black; postmedial line brown; both lines with a black spot on costa; subterminal line present but indistinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,597,848,874]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Reniform: indistinct, almost invisible.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,358,891,917]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Hindwing: brown</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,515,934,960]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Underside: unicolorous brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,675,1003]" box="[151,774,977,1003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Abdomen: brown with a black crest on first segment.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,353,1063,1089]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,452,1106,1132]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ovipositor: quadrangular.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,900,1149,1175]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Anterior apophyses: length equal to that of posterior apophyses.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,966,1189,1219]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
8 
<superScript attach="left" box="[165,177,1189,1203]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">th</superScript>
abdominal segment: very narrow, ventrally fused with 7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[841,853,1189,1203]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">th</superScript>
segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
7 
<superScript attach="left" box="[165,177,1233,1247]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">th</superScript>
abdominal segment: heavily sclerotised, anteriorly with an irregular, triangular, apically narrow extension. Antrum: short, tapered, heavily sclerotised.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Ductus bursae: membranous, long, coiling by antrum; ostium and ductus bursae 2 X as long as corpus bursae. Appendix bursae: arising posteriorly from ductus bursae immediately after antrum.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1063,1434]" box="[151,439,1408,1434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Corpus bursae: globular.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,971,1494,1564]" box="[151,412,1494,1520]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,971,1494,1564]" box="[151,971,1538,1564]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The female genitalia resemble those of 
<emphasis box="[613,701,1538,1563]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2007" box="[613,697,1538,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Tolpia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="odor">T. odor</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
see under that species.
</paragraph>
